    <section class="main-content">
      <h2>What Is New Equipment Financing?</h2>
      
      <p>New equipment financing is a loan specifically for buying brand-new machinery, vehicles, or equipment. The lender pays the supplier directly, and you repay in monthly instalments.</p>
      
      <p><strong>How it's different from a regular business loan:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Lower rates</strong> — Because the equipment is collateral, rates are typically 1-2% lower than unsecured loans</li>
        <li><strong>Longer terms</strong> — Up to 7 years for heavy equipment (vs 3-5 years for most business loans)</li>
        <li><strong>Easier approval</strong> — The equipment itself backs the loan, so credit requirements are often more flexible</li>
        <li><strong>Tax benefits</strong> — You can claim capital allowances on the equipment, reducing your taxable income</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why Finance New Equipment Instead of Used?</h2>
      
      <p>We get this question a lot. Here's the honest comparison:</p>
      
      <div class="comparison-table">
        <h3>New Equipment vs Used Equipment Financing</h3>
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Factor</th>
              <th>New Equipment</th>
              <th>Used Equipment</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Interest Rate</strong></td>
              <td>3.5-5% per year</td>
              <td>5-8% per year</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Loan Amount</strong></td>
              <td>Up to 100% of price</td>
              <td>Up to 80% of value</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Repayment Term</strong></td>
              <td>5-7 years</td>
              <td>3-5 years</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Warranty Coverage</strong></td>
              <td>Full manufacturer warranty (1-3 years)</td>
              <td>Limited or no warranty</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Maintenance Costs</strong></td>
              <td>Low (first 3-5 years)</td>
              <td>Higher (immediate repairs likely)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>Approval Speed</strong></td>
              <td>Faster (clear valuation)</td>
              <td>Slower (valuation needed)</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      
      <p><strong>Bottom line:</strong> New equipment costs more upfront, but you get better rates, longer terms, and peace of mind. For businesses relying on equipment daily (construction, logistics, manufacturing), downtime from breakdowns costs more than the premium for new.</p>

      <h2>How Much Does New Equipment Financing Cost?</h2>
      
      <p>Let's break down a real example. Say you're buying a new excavator for RM400,000:</p>
      
      <div class="example-box">
        <h3>Example: RM400,000 New Excavator</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Equipment Price:</strong> RM400,000</li>
          <li><strong>Down Payment (10%):</strong> RM40,000</li>
          <li><strong>Loan Amount:</strong> RM360,000</li>
          <li><strong>Interest Rate:</strong> 4.2% per year</li>
          <li><strong>Repayment Term:</strong> 7 years</li>
          <li><strong>Monthly Payment:</strong> RM4,950</li>
          <li><strong>Total Interest:</strong> RM56,040 over 7 years</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p><strong>The math that matters:</strong> If that excavator earns you RM15,000-RM20,000 per month on projects, the RM4,950 monthly payment is very manageable. You're cash-flow positive from month one.</p>
      </div>

