          <p>Equipment is yours to use. Monthly repayments start the following month.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p><strong>Timeline:</strong> Most of our clients go from quotation to equipment delivery in 7-14 days.</p>

      <h2>Tax Benefits: Capital Allowance Explained</h2>
      <p>Here's a bonus: New equipment financing comes with tax advantages.</p>
      
      <p>Under Malaysian tax law, you can claim <strong>capital allowances</strong> on business equipment. This reduces your taxable income, which means lower tax bills.</p>
      
      <div class="tax-example">
        <h3>How Capital Allowance Works:</h3>
        <p>Let's say you buy a new lorry for RM200,000. Here's how capital allowance saves you money:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Initial Allowance (Year 1):</strong> 20% = RM40,000 deduction</li>
          <li><strong>Annual Allowance (Years 1-5):</strong> 20% per year = RM40,000/year deduction</li>
          <li><strong>Total deductions:</strong> RM40,000 (initial) + RM200,000 (annual over 5 years) = RM240,000</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>If your company pays 24% corporate tax, that RM240,000 in deductions saves you approximately <strong>RM57,600 in taxes</strong> over 5 years.</p>
        
        <p><em>(Note: Capital allowance rates vary by equipment type. Check with your accountant or LHDN guidelines for specifics.)</em></p>
      </div>

      <h2>Common Questions About New Equipment Financing</h2>
      
      <div class="faq">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I finance 100% of the equipment cost?</h3>
          <p>Some lenders offer 100% financing for established businesses with strong credit. Most require 10-20% down payment. The down payment reduces your monthly payment and often gets you better rates.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What if my business is less than 2 years old?</h3>
          <p>It's tougher, but not impossible. If you have strong sales, existing contracts, or personal assets to put up as additional collateral, we can work with that. Some lenders are more flexible for high-growth startups.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I trade in my old equipment as down payment?</h3>
          <p>Yes! If you're upgrading, many suppliers accept trade-ins. The trade-in value counts toward your down payment, reducing the loan amount needed.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What happens if I want to sell the equipment before the loan is paid off?</h3>
          <p>You can sell it, but you'll need to settle the remaining loan balance first (from the sale proceeds). If you're upgrading, some lenders offer refinancing options.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Is there a penalty for early repayment?</h3>
          <p>Depends on the lender. Some charge a small penalty (1-3% of outstanding balance), others don't. We always clarify this before you sign.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How does new equipment financing compare to leasing?</h3>
          <p>Financing means you OWN the equipment from day one (with the lender holding a charge until paid off). Leasing means you rent it long-term. Financing is usually better if you plan to use the equipment for 5+ years. Leasing can make sense for equipment that gets outdated quickly (tech, software-based systems).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

